    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "That I know.\nModify the greeter_server.js sayHello function\n\n``` js\n/**\n * Implements the SayHello RPC method.\n */\nfunction sayHello(call, callback) {\n  try {\n    callback(null, []); // throws \"Illegal value for Message.Field .helloworld.HelloReply.message of type string: object (no array expected)\"\n  } catch(err) {\n    // caught but callback with error does not reach client\n    // clients waits on callback\n    callback(err);  \n  }\n}\n```\n\nWhen gRPC fails or in this case protobuf, there is no way to tell the client.\nI know that this case should not happen if a RPC function is implemented correctly. But I saw a client waiting for a callback two times already because the callback result value was \"illegal\".\n\nAn grpc.status.INTERNAL error response or a way to callback again when the callback fails would be nice.\n"
  },
